'''Bazoumana Touré''' (born 2 March 2006) is an Ivorian professional [[Association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[Winger (association football)|winger]] for German {{German football updater|Hoffenhe}} club [[TSG Hoffenheim]] and the [[Ivory Coast national football team|Ivory Coast national team]].

==Youth career==
Touré began his career at Ivorian club [[ASEC Mimosas]], widely regarded as the biggest club in [[Ivory Coast]], playing for the youth team until 2022, when he was promoted to the first team.

==Club career==
===ASEC Mimosas===
Touré played his first season for Ivorian club [[ASEC Mimosas]] in the [[2022–23 Ligue 1 (Ivory Coast)|2022–23 season]], scoring his first goal in a 4–0 home win over [[AS Indenié Abengourou]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.flashscore.fr/match/ObiWphTb/#/resume-du-match|title=ASEC Mimosas 4-0 Abengourou|publisher=flashscore.fr|language=fr}}</ref> He helped them towards first place that year, earning the league title.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.national-football-teams.com/club/495/2022_1/Asec_Mimosas_Abidjan.html|title=ASEC Mimosas win Ligue 1|publisher=national-football-teams.com}}</ref>

===Hammarby===
Touré signed for Swedish [[Allsvenskan]] club [[Hammarby Fotboll|Hammarby IF]] in early 2024, after an extensive trial and training period.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.hammarbyfotboll.se/spelare/herr/bazoumana-toure|title=Touré signs for Hammarby|publisher=hammarbyfotboll.se|language=sv}}</ref> He made his debut in a 2-1 away defeat to [[Halmstads BK|Halmstad]],<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://ie.soccerway.com/matches/2024/04/25/sweden/allsvenskan/halmstads-bollklubb/hammarby/4284298/|title=Halmstads 2-1 Hammarby:Touré debut|publisher=soccerway.com}}</ref> quickly establishing himself as a regular in the side, even at just 18 years of age.

Touré scored his first Hammarby goal in a 3-0 home victory over [[IK Sirius Fotboll|Sirius]],<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://ie.soccerway.com/matches/2024/05/26/sweden/allsvenskan/hammarby/sirius/4284343/|title=Hammarby 3-0 Sirius:Touré first goal|publisher=soccerway.com}}</ref> adding to his tally for the season with goals against [[Djurgårdens IF Fotboll|Djurgården]],<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://ie.soccerway.com/matches/2024/06/02/sweden/allsvenskan/djurgardens-fotbollsforening/hammarby/4284350/|title=Djurgardens 0-3 Hammarby|publisher=soccerway.com}}</ref> [[IF Brommapojkarna|Brommapojkarna]]<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://ie.soccerway.com/matches/2024/07/20/sweden/allsvenskan/ildrottsforening--brommapojkarna/hammarby/4284381/|title=Brommapojkarna 0-2 Hammarby|publisher=soccerway.com}}</ref> and [[Halmstads BK|Halmstad]],<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://ie.soccerway.com/matches/2024/10/05/sweden/allsvenskan/hammarby/halmstads-bollklubb/4284464/|title=Hammarby 1-0 Halmstads|publisher=soccerway.com}}</ref> as well as another two against Brommapojkarna a month later<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://ie.soccerway.com/matches/2024/08/12/sweden/allsvenskan/hammarby/ildrottsforening--brommapojkarna/4284399/|title=Brommapojkarna 3-3 Hammarby|publisher=soccerway.com}}</ref> and another two against [[IK Sirius Fotboll|Sirius]]<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://ie.soccerway.com/matches/2024/10/26/sweden/allsvenskan/sirius/hammarby/4284482/|title=Sirius 0-3 Hammarby|publisher=soccerway.com}}</ref> also, bringing his tally to 8 goals in 23 [[Allsvenskan]] games.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.tntsports.co.uk/football/bazoumana-toure_prs691632/person.shtml|title=Touré 2024 stats|publisher=tntsports.com}}</ref>

===Hoffenheim===
====2024–25====
On 1 February 2025, Touré signed a long-term contract with German club [[TSG Hoffenheim]] for a sum around €14 million plus €2 million in bonuses.<ref>{{cite web|publisher=TSG Hoffenheim|url=https://www.tsg-hoffenheim.de/en/news/overview/2025/02/tsg-sign-top-ivorian-talent-bazoumana-toure|title=TSG sign top Ivorian talent Bazoumana Touré|date=1 February 2025|access-date=1 February 2025}}</ref> Touré made 13 appearances for Hoffenheim in his first half season at the club, registering 3 assists in 7 starts, including two assists for [[Andrej Kramaric]] against [[1.FSV Mainz 05]] in a 2-0 win.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/live/c33z760k3g6t|title=Hoffenheim 2-0 Mainz|website=BBC}}</ref>

====2025–26====
Touré scored his first [[Bundesliga]] goal in a 3–0 away win over [[FC St. Pauli|St. Pauli]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.bundesliga.com/en/bundesliga/news/st-pauli-hoffenheim-match-report-highlights-matchday-7-34470|title=Andrej Kramarić shines as Hoffenheim continue perfect away form with win at St. Pauli|website=Bundesliga}}</ref> Touré finished the season with 5 goals and 9 assists in 29 starts,<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://theanalyst.com/players/5608/bazoumana-toure/stats|title=2025-26 Bazoumana Touré stats|website=Opta Analyst|access-date=28 May 2026}}</ref> as [[TSG Hoffenheim|Hoffenheim]] finished [[2025-26 TSG 1899 Hoffenheim season|5th]] to qualify for the [[2026-27 UEFA Europa League]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.tsg-hoffenheim.de/en/news/overview/2026/05/tsg-hoffenheim-will-play-in-the-uefa-europa-league#:~:text=Following%20their%200%2D4%20defeat,UEFA%20Europa%20League%20next%20season.|title=TSG Hoffenheim will play in the UEFA Europa League|website=TSG Hoffenheim|access-date=28 May 2026}}</ref>

==International career==
Touré played for the [[Ivory Coast national under-20 football team|Ivory Coast U20 side]], making 3 appearances. On 27 May 2025, he was called up to the [[Ivory Coast national under-23 football team|Ivory Coast U23]]s for a friendly.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://mondialsport.ci/amical-u23-issa-fofana-abakar-sylla-malick-yalcouye-richard-kone-la-liste-des-elephanteaux-face-a-la-hollande-28847.sport|title=Amical U23 : Issa Fofana, Abakar Sylla, Malick Yalcouyé, Richard Koné, … la liste des Eléphanteaux face à la Hollande|first=NAS|last=SARL|date=24 May 2025|website=Mondialsport.ci}}</ref>

Touré received his first [[Ivory Coast national football team|senior]] call-up in September 2025, before making his debut in a 7–0 win over [[Seychelles national football team|Seychelles]] in October 2025.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.bundesliga.com/en/bundesliga/news/who-is-bazoumana-toure-hoffenheim-ivory-coast-winger-35072|title=Bazoumana Touré: Who is Hoffenheim's explosive, young Ivorian winger?|website=bundesliga.com}}</ref> 
In December 2025, Touré was announced in [[2025 Africa Cup of Nations squads#Group F#Ivory Coast|Ivory Coast's 2025 AFCON squad]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://sportnewsafrica.com/en/posts/afcon-2025-bazoumana-toure-to-eclipse-nicolas-pepe-forget-for-ivory-coast|title=AFCON 2025: Bazoumana Touré to eclipse Nicolas Pépé forget for Ivory Coast|first=PHILEMON|last=MBALE|date=16 December 2025|website=sportnewsafrica.com}}</ref> During the tournament, Touré scored his first international goal with a 90th minute winner versus [[Gabon national football team|Gabon]] in a 3-2 victory.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/live/c0je0xzg3zvt|title=Afcon 2025:Gabon 2-3 Ivory Coast:Elephants top group on goal difference|website=bbc.com}}</ref>

Touré was named in the Ivory Coast's final 26-man squad for the [[2026 FIFA World Cup]] in May 2026.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.fifa.com/en/tournaments/mens/worldcup/canadamexicousa2026/articles/cote-divoire-squad-announcement-emerse-fae|title=Côte d'Ivoire squad announcement-2026 FIFA World Cup}}</ref>

==Style of play==
Bazoumana Touré has been described as an explosive, highly creative inverted left winger who thrives on high-speed transitions, isolated 1v1 situations, and high-volume crossing. Touré is right-footed, although he has predominantly been used on the left wing, allowing him to cut inside onto his stronger foot or drive to the byline, he has also been deployed briefly as a [[Forward (association football)#centre-forward|centre-forward]] and on the right wing with [[TSG Hoffenheim|Hoffenheim]].
Touré possesses blistering speed, a tendency for early crosses, a penchant for dribbling and a high work rate, being likened to fellow [[Bundesliga]] player [[Karim Adeyemi]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.bundesliga.com/en/bundesliga/news/who-is-bazoumana-toure-hoffenheim-ivory-coast-winger-35072|title=Bazoumana Touré: Who is Hoffenheim's explosive, young Ivorian winger?|website=Bundesliga|date=8 December 2025|access-date=28 May 2026}}</ref>

==Personal life==
Bazoumana Touré grew up in the Abidjan district of Anoumabo, starting his career at local club Magic System FC.<ref>{{cite web |title="Kan nå lika långt som Odilon" – Fotboll Sthlm möter Bazoumana Touré. (in Swedish) |url=https://fotbollsthlm.se/hammarby/kan-na-lika-langt-som-odilon-fotboll-sthlm-moter-bazoumana-toure/ |website=Fotboll Sthlm |access-date=4 December 2024}}</ref> His father worked at the Ivorian milk company Saprolait.

